dataStructure.name: sid.org.tmforum.tip.resource.res.log.os.PartyRoleLicenseOSDetails
dataStructure.description:
This class defines the semantics of the PartyRoleLicensesOS association. Its attributes help specify the licensing details for this particular OperatingSystem instance.This association defines the semantics of how a given PartyRole legally uses particular OS Features.

This association class is optional
dataStructure.label: PartyRoleLicenseOSDetails

child.name: maxNumberOSLicenses
child.description:
This attribute defines the maximum number of licenses that be allotted for this particular OperatingSystem instance.

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional
child.label: maxNumberOSLicenses

child.name: currentNumberOSLicenses
child.description:
This attribute defines the current number of licenses that have been allotted for this particular OperatingSystem instance.

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional
child.label: currentNumberOSLicenses

child.name: licenseValidityTimePeriod
child.description:
This attribute defines a time period for which this license for this particular OperatingSystem is valid. A TimePeriod is a complex attribute, consisting of a Date and a TimeStamp for the starting period of the license and a Date and a TimeStamp for the ending period of the license.

This element is generated from an attribute.

This attribute is optional
child.label: licenseValidityTimePeriod
